106
00:06:11,038 --> 00:06:15,174
            narrator:           
 several american towns claim to
be the birthplace of the sundae.

107
00:06:15,176 --> 00:06:17,842
     sundaes first appeared     
          in the 1880s,         

108
00:06:17,844 --> 00:06:21,446
when the sale of ice cream sodas
     was banned on sundays.     

109
00:06:21,448 --> 00:06:25,583
instead, soda-fountain operators
 poured soda syrup on ice cream,

110
00:06:25,585 --> 00:06:29,154
   added toppings, and called   
   this new treat the sundae.   

111
00:06:30,257 --> 00:06:33,191
                     ♪          

112
00:06:33,193 --> 00:06:35,461
  today, ice cream sundaes come 

113
00:06:35,463 --> 00:06:38,597
       pre-made and frozen      
     in individual servings.    

114
00:06:38,599 --> 00:06:40,398
    there's no need to wait.    

115
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:45,004
  this decadent dessert can be  
    served up in an instant.    

116
00:06:45,006 --> 00:06:47,339
     at the sundae factory,     
       productions starts       

117
00:06:47,341 --> 00:06:50,142
      with something called     
       the white base mix.      

118
00:06:50,144 --> 00:06:53,478
    it's a pasteurized blend    
      of fresh cream, milk,     

119
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:57,082
  and a variety of sweeteners.  

120
00:06:57,084 --> 00:06:59,284
      a worker adds a blend     
       of yellow coloring       

121
00:06:59,286 --> 00:07:00,753
     to the white base mix,     

122
00:07:00,755 --> 00:07:02,687
        and this takes it       
        from bright white       

123
00:07:02,689 --> 00:07:04,123
        to an off-white.        

124
00:07:06,227 --> 00:07:08,961
       a generous helping       
     of pure vanilla extract    

125
00:07:08,963 --> 00:07:10,695
   lends a distinctive flavor   

126
00:07:10,697 --> 00:07:14,032
      and adds extra color      
       to the cream base.       

127
00:07:14,034 --> 00:07:18,570
 after a final stir, the mix is 
  ready for a freezing process, 

128
00:07:18,572 --> 00:07:20,405
 during which, air will be added

129
00:07:20,407 --> 00:07:24,376
         to turn the mix        
      into soft ice cream.      

130
00:07:24,378 --> 00:07:26,711
it's time to cue the containers.

131
00:07:26,713 --> 00:07:30,715
 two at a time, individual-sized
    sundae cups move forward    

132
00:07:30,717 --> 00:07:33,385
     on the production line.    

133
00:07:33,387 --> 00:07:35,554
        they meet up with       
    the ice cream dispenser.    

134
00:07:38,125 --> 00:07:40,392
     it automatically pumps     
         precise amounts        

135
00:07:40,394 --> 00:07:43,295
  of the soft vanilla ice cream 
         into the cups.         

136
00:07:47,601 --> 00:07:50,002
        it fills the cups       
        to the 3/4 mark,        

137
00:07:50,004 --> 00:07:52,438
     leaving plenty of room     
          for toppings.         

138
00:07:54,942 --> 00:07:56,341
    it's now time to prepare    

139
00:07:56,343 --> 00:07:58,944
         the next layer         
       of deliciousness --      

140
00:07:58,946 --> 00:08:01,413
   the chocolate fudge sauce.   

141
00:08:01,415 --> 00:08:03,014
    a worker mixes skim milk    

142
00:08:03,016 --> 00:08:05,684
         and sweeteners         
    to a frothy consistency,    

143
00:08:05,686 --> 00:08:11,156
and then adds several large bags
       of dark rich cocoa.      

144
00:08:11,158 --> 00:08:14,360
    the mixer paddle agitates   
  the ingredients to distribute 

145
00:08:14,362 --> 00:08:16,895
  the cocoa evenly throughout.  

146
00:08:20,100 --> 00:08:22,968
  the chocolate fudge is pumped 
       into a plastic tote      

147
00:08:22,970 --> 00:08:25,304
       to cool overnight.       

148
00:08:25,306 --> 00:08:26,504
         during cooling,        

149
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:29,308
      the sauce thickens up     
         substantially.         

150
00:08:32,446 --> 00:08:35,847
         it's now a rich        
     chocolate fudge syrup.     

151
00:08:35,849 --> 00:08:39,584
  velvety smooth, the chocolate 
   syrup flows out of the tote  

152
00:08:39,586 --> 00:08:41,420
      and into a big tank.      

153
00:08:43,257 --> 00:08:46,591
  from there, nozzles dispense  
    the chocolate fudge syrup   

154
00:08:46,593 --> 00:08:51,129
   onto the vanilla ice cream   
          in the cups.          

155
00:08:51,131 --> 00:08:53,932
      next, a worker pours      
     a liquid-topping blend     

156
00:08:53,934 --> 00:08:56,068
 into a high-speed mixer system 

157
00:08:56,070 --> 00:08:58,470
          that beats it         
    to a whipped consistency.   

158
00:09:01,475 --> 00:09:03,542
         nozzles deposit        
       the whipped topping      

159
00:09:03,544 --> 00:09:07,279
     onto the syrup-covered     
           ice cream.           

160
00:09:07,281 --> 00:09:09,748
      now it's time to add      
      some chocolate crunch     

161
00:09:09,750 --> 00:09:12,117
  to the smooth, sweet sundae.  

162
00:09:14,154 --> 00:09:17,022
      the system sprinkles      
   semi-sweet chocolate chunks  

163
00:09:17,024 --> 00:09:20,359
    onto the whipped topping.   

164
00:09:20,361 --> 00:09:23,095
      it's the final touch.     

165
00:09:23,097 --> 00:09:25,364
       these single-serve       
        chocolate sundaes       

166
00:09:25,366 --> 00:09:30,368
       have been prepared       
  almost entirely by machines.  

167
00:09:30,370 --> 00:09:33,905
    a conveyor now sends them   
   through an icy blast of air  

168
00:09:33,907 --> 00:09:35,441
       for a quick freeze.      

169
00:09:38,245 --> 00:09:42,114
 exiting the freezer, the frozen
     sundaes travel forward,    

170
00:09:42,116 --> 00:09:46,518
   shielded by overhead guards  
    for food-safety reasons.    

171
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:49,754
       the sundaes funnel       
    into a single-file lane.    

172
00:09:49,756 --> 00:09:52,391
       this positions them      
        to receive lids.        

173
00:09:55,396 --> 00:09:58,062
   the lids slide down a chute  
         and land on top        

174
00:09:58,064 --> 00:10:01,132
  of the ice cream sundae cups. 

175
00:10:01,134 --> 00:10:03,802
     rollers press the lids     
        down on the rims.       

176
00:10:06,407 --> 00:10:10,776
 a revolving apparatus deposits 
plastic collars around the lids.

177
00:10:13,814 --> 00:10:17,282
  moving forward, the machinery 
      sorts the sundae cups     

178
00:10:17,284 --> 00:10:19,084
         in row of two.         

179
00:10:19,086 --> 00:10:21,553
       this allows a robot      
      with suctioning arms      

180
00:10:21,555 --> 00:10:23,588
    to pick up six at a time    

181
00:10:23,590 --> 00:10:27,893
          and pack them         
      into a cardboard box.     

182
00:10:27,895 --> 00:10:30,962
 the boxes travel under and over
          packing tape          

183
00:10:30,964 --> 00:10:33,132
  to seal the tops and bottoms. 

184
00:10:37,037 --> 00:10:41,506
    incredibly, this factory    
    produces 1,440 ice cream    

185
00:10:41,508 --> 00:10:45,244
  sundae cups every 15 minutes. 

186
00:10:45,246 --> 00:10:49,847
     and it's all thanks to     
   the magic of mechanization.  

187
00:10:49,849 --> 00:10:53,385
 this company also produces tubs
     of flavored ice cream,     

188
00:10:53,387 --> 00:10:55,654
        so there are many       
     mouth-watering choices     

189
00:10:55,656 --> 00:10:58,123
           to be made           
        at dessert time.        

190
00:10:58,125 --> 00:11:03,829
                     ♪          

191
