192
00:11:15,409 --> 00:11:18,676
  narrator: digital painting is 
    a relatively new medium.    

193
00:11:18,678 --> 00:11:20,279
  it's an artistic hybrid that  

194
00:11:20,281 --> 00:11:22,481
         marries modern         
       computer technology      

195
00:11:22,483 --> 00:11:25,617
    with traditional painting   
       by hand on canvas.       

196
00:11:25,619 --> 00:11:29,020
 today, some photography studios
     offer digital painting     

197
00:11:29,022 --> 00:11:31,756
      as a way to transform     
     photographic portraits     

198
00:11:31,758 --> 00:11:33,525
     into painted portraits.    

199
00:11:37,230 --> 00:11:41,366
  this specialized photographer 
     offers digital painting    

200
00:11:41,368 --> 00:11:43,835
  to enhance original portraits 

201
00:11:43,837 --> 00:11:47,238
    and cherished snapshots.    

202
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:49,174
   his studio also specializes  

203
00:11:49,176 --> 00:11:52,044
in creating life-story collages.

204
00:11:52,046 --> 00:11:53,845
  the in-house artist assembles 

205
00:11:53,847 --> 00:11:55,714
    photos and illustrations,   

206
00:11:55,716 --> 00:11:56,782
       depicting elements       

207
00:11:56,784 --> 00:11:59,584
   of the subject's lifetime.   

208
00:11:59,586 --> 00:12:02,387
 she scans and digitizes photos 

209
00:12:02,389 --> 00:12:05,590
 which are not already digital. 

210
00:12:05,592 --> 00:12:08,927
     she manually retouches     
 every image with a digital pen 

211
00:12:08,929 --> 00:12:11,597
           and tablet           
    to maximize the quality.    

212
00:12:18,539 --> 00:12:21,740
     then she begins working    
  on the layout of the collage. 

213
00:12:25,545 --> 00:12:27,746
     once she has finalized     
           the layout,          

214
00:12:27,748 --> 00:12:30,081
      she blends the edges      
          of each image         

215
00:12:30,083 --> 00:12:32,216
      so that the elements      
         flow seamlessly        

216
00:12:32,218 --> 00:12:33,452
        into each other.        

217
00:12:35,422 --> 00:12:39,558
      now the artist begins     
       digitally painting.      

218
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:43,095
  she chooses from a selection  
   of brush shapes and sizes,   

219
00:12:43,097 --> 00:12:45,264
  and from a myriad of colors.  

220
00:12:51,638 --> 00:12:54,840
    she applies digital paint   
     to blur the hard lines     

221
00:12:54,842 --> 00:12:56,041
       of the photographs       

222
00:12:56,043 --> 00:12:59,044
     to make them look more     
      like painted images.      

223
00:13:03,717 --> 00:13:05,049
      this painting process     

224
00:13:05,051 --> 00:13:09,788
       takes several hours      
      of painstaking work.      

225
00:13:09,790 --> 00:13:12,724
 she sends the digital painting 
      to the lab technician     

226
00:13:12,726 --> 00:13:15,861
      who prepares to print     
     the work onto a canvas.    

227
00:13:18,399 --> 00:13:21,199
        first, he tweaks        
      the entire painting,      

228
00:13:21,201 --> 00:13:24,036
    balancing the brightness    
         and the colors.        

229
00:13:31,078 --> 00:13:33,077
  he prints a small test sample 

230
00:13:33,079 --> 00:13:36,013
           on canvas.           

231
00:13:36,015 --> 00:13:37,682
       both the technician      
         and the artist         

232
00:13:37,684 --> 00:13:41,686
 meticulously examine the sample
      under magnification,      

233
00:13:41,688 --> 00:13:44,890
    looking for any painting    
       or printing errors.      

234
00:13:44,892 --> 00:13:46,625
    if everything is perfect,   

235
00:13:46,627 --> 00:13:50,695
 the technician installs a large
   canvas roll on the printer.  

236
00:13:50,697 --> 00:13:53,631
       the machine prints,      
     not with regular inks,     

237
00:13:53,633 --> 00:13:55,100
   but with archival pigments,  

238
00:13:55,102 --> 00:13:59,037
    which last for centuries.   

239
00:13:59,039 --> 00:14:00,505
        after each pass,        

240
00:14:00,507 --> 00:14:02,240
   the head waits six seconds   

241
00:14:02,242 --> 00:14:04,109
    to let the pigments dry.    

242
00:14:04,111 --> 00:14:08,780
this prevents them from smearing
        on the next pass.       

243
00:14:08,782 --> 00:14:12,317
  a digital painting this size  
   takes five hours to print.   

244
00:14:14,454 --> 00:14:17,456
      the pigments must dry     
          for 72 hours          

245
00:14:17,458 --> 00:14:20,359
   to ensure they're embedded   
        into the canvas.        

246
00:14:20,361 --> 00:14:23,795
   then the technician applies  
  a coat of stabilizing lacquer 

247
00:14:23,797 --> 00:14:25,730
           to protect           
     the surface from damage    

248
00:14:25,732 --> 00:14:29,801
   caused by ultraviolet rays   
          or handling.          

249
00:14:29,803 --> 00:14:32,770
     the lacquer takes about    
         an hour to dry.        

250
00:14:32,772 --> 00:14:34,806
      then they can safely      
        mount the canvas        

251
00:14:34,808 --> 00:14:37,542
      on a stretcher frame.     

252
00:14:37,544 --> 00:14:40,344
    the workers pull it tight   
       with special pliers      

253
00:14:40,346 --> 00:14:42,247
    and then staple it down.    

254
00:14:45,018 --> 00:14:48,019
      they cut the corners      
     to facilitate framing.     

255
00:14:50,123 --> 00:14:53,024
 the artist applies a white gel 
   with thicker brush strokes   

256
00:14:53,026 --> 00:14:54,626
          in some areas         

257
00:14:54,628 --> 00:14:58,296
   and thinner ones in others.  

258
00:14:58,298 --> 00:15:01,900
      this gives the print      
   the texture of a painting.   

259
00:15:01,902 --> 00:15:06,972
       the gel turns clear      
    as it dries for 24 hours.   

260
00:15:06,974 --> 00:15:09,574
     then the artist paints     
    the entire printed canvas   

261
00:15:09,576 --> 00:15:11,976
      with acrylic paints.      

262
00:15:11,978 --> 00:15:14,780
     as she applies shading     
       and creates depth,       

263
00:15:14,782 --> 00:15:18,983
     the painting gradually     
          comes alive.          

264
00:15:18,985 --> 00:15:22,854
       when she finishes,       
       she signs her work.      

265
00:15:22,856 --> 00:15:25,523
        in about an hour,       
        the paint is dry        

266
00:15:25,525 --> 00:15:28,527
   and the digital painting is  
       ready for framing.       

267
00:15:33,934 --> 00:15:37,536
   she inserts a personalized   
  certificate of authenticity,  

268
00:15:37,538 --> 00:15:40,472
      stating that this is      
      a one-of-a-kind work,     

269
00:15:40,474 --> 00:15:43,008
   and applies the photography  
         studio's label         

270
00:15:43,010 --> 00:15:45,877
   on the back of the canvas.   

271
00:15:45,879 --> 00:15:48,746
         whether it's a         
   creatively-crafted collage   

272
00:15:48,748 --> 00:15:51,216
        or produced from        
      a simple photograph,      

273
00:15:51,218 --> 00:15:54,286
       a digital painting       
  immortalizes precious moments 

274
00:15:54,288 --> 00:15:56,821
  captured by the camera lens.  

275
00:15:56,823 --> 00:15:57,823
                     ♪          

276
00:16:05,365 --> 00:16:10,568
                     ♪          

277
00:16:10,570 --> 00:16:12,971
     narrator: at some point    
    in 19th-century england,    

278
00:16:12,973 --> 00:16:14,506
       a new game evolved       

279
00:16:14,508 --> 00:16:16,574
     that took its name from    
     the duke of beaufort's     

280
00:16:16,576 --> 00:16:17,976
        badminton house.        

281
00:16:17,978 --> 00:16:20,111
      badminton soon became     
          all the rage          

282
00:16:20,113 --> 00:16:22,581
among british officers in india.

283
00:16:22,583 --> 00:16:26,450
 today, fans believe the game is
 faster and harder than tennis, 

284
00:16:26,452 --> 00:16:28,420
      its long-time rival.      

285
00:16:31,992 --> 00:16:33,858
            to create           
     the carbon-fiber shafts    

286
00:16:33,860 --> 00:16:35,593
   of the badminton racquets,   

287
00:16:35,595 --> 00:16:37,529
        the manufacturer        
        follows a series        

288
00:16:37,531 --> 00:16:41,533
     of meticulously-defined    
        production steps.       

289
00:16:41,535 --> 00:16:43,935
       the process begins       
       by tightly wrapping      

290
00:16:43,937 --> 00:16:46,470
     a carbon-fiber fabric,     
         called prepreg,        

291
00:16:46,472 --> 00:16:49,340
      multiple times around     
        a metal cylinder.       

292
00:16:49,342 --> 00:16:52,076
        a worker encases        
      the fabric in plastic     

293
00:16:52,078 --> 00:16:54,546
  to hold the prepreg in place. 

294
00:16:54,548 --> 00:16:57,215
 then he suspends the cylinders 
           from a rack          

295
00:16:57,217 --> 00:16:59,184
  and rolls them into an oven.  

296
00:17:01,888 --> 00:17:05,890
 the heating process transforms 
       the wrapped prepreg      

297
00:17:05,892 --> 00:17:08,093
     into solid lightweight     
        and super-strong        

298
00:17:08,095 --> 00:17:10,695
     carbon-fiber material.     

299
00:17:10,697 --> 00:17:13,164
     this specialized device    
      removes the cylinder      

300
00:17:13,166 --> 00:17:14,833
     from the carbon fiber,     

301
00:17:14,835 --> 00:17:17,502
     leaving a hollow shaft.    

302
00:17:17,504 --> 00:17:20,237
   here, we can see the stages  
     of production required     

303
00:17:20,239 --> 00:17:24,843
      to create the hollow      
       carbon-fiber shaft.      

304
00:17:24,845 --> 00:17:28,446
in the next stage of production,
   a worker begins the process  

305
00:17:28,448 --> 00:17:31,249
        of manufacturing        
       the racquet frame.       

306
00:17:31,251 --> 00:17:33,117
         she starts with        
     a different formulation    

307
00:17:33,119 --> 00:17:34,786
      of prepreg material,      

308
00:17:34,788 --> 00:17:37,222
         which she folds        
        into thin strips.       

309
00:17:39,726 --> 00:17:43,928
     the key is to make sure    
    each strip is identical.    

310
00:17:43,930 --> 00:17:45,129
       in the next phase,       

311
00:17:45,131 --> 00:17:48,799
    a worker wraps the strip    
   around a purpose-built mold  

312
00:17:48,801 --> 00:17:51,202
       to create the shape      
       of a racquet frame.      

313
00:17:54,608 --> 00:17:58,343
 she introduces the carbon-fiber
      shaft into the mold.      

314
00:17:58,345 --> 00:18:01,412
  the racquet is taking shape.  

315
00:18:01,414 --> 00:18:03,148
  another piece of carbon fiber 

316
00:18:03,150 --> 00:18:06,484
  forms the joint between them. 

317
00:18:06,486 --> 00:18:08,986
        the frame-shaped        
      prepreg carbon fiber      

318
00:18:08,988 --> 00:18:11,155
         then goes into         
       a shaping machine,       

319
00:18:11,157 --> 00:18:13,758
       and the lid closes.      

320
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:17,228
    the shaping machine heats   
   and then cools the prepreg   

321
00:18:17,230 --> 00:18:19,531
         over the course        
      of about 30 minutes.      

322
00:18:21,568 --> 00:18:23,101
     a worker lifts the lid     

323
00:18:23,103 --> 00:18:25,636
  and removes the fully-formed  
         racquet frame,         

324
00:18:25,638 --> 00:18:27,339
     which has excess resin.    

325
00:18:30,777 --> 00:18:33,244
  resin holds the carbon fibers 
            together            

326
00:18:33,246 --> 00:18:35,246
   before the curing process.   

327
00:18:35,248 --> 00:18:37,181
    heating expels the resin,   

328
00:18:37,183 --> 00:18:40,585
   which must then be removed.  

329
00:18:40,587 --> 00:18:43,387
       a narrow bit drills      
   the first sequence of holes  

330
00:18:43,389 --> 00:18:44,856
      in an offset pattern      

331
00:18:44,858 --> 00:18:47,292
       to make the racquet      
        easier to string.       

332
00:18:49,596 --> 00:18:52,664
    a larger-gauge bit drills   
       holes large enough       

333
00:18:52,666 --> 00:18:55,100
      to permit two strings     
        to pass through.        

334
00:18:57,804 --> 00:19:01,405
   quality-control inspectors   
choose a racquet frame at random

335
00:19:01,407 --> 00:19:03,474
        to test how much        
      pressure it can bear      

336
00:19:03,476 --> 00:19:05,710
        before it reaches       
       the breaking point.      

337
00:19:10,684 --> 00:19:13,150
    it's finally time to add    
        the wooden handle       

338
00:19:13,152 --> 00:19:16,454
      and cap to the shaft      
  and put everything together.  

339
00:19:19,626 --> 00:19:21,826
      the racquets head for     
    the painting department,    

340
00:19:21,828 --> 00:19:24,696
 where they receive a base coat.

341
00:19:24,698 --> 00:19:29,100
 then workers meticulously apply
       a series of decals.      

342
00:19:29,102 --> 00:19:30,835
    the decals soak in water    

343
00:19:30,837 --> 00:19:33,271
        to make it easier       
     to remove the backing.     

344
00:19:38,779 --> 00:19:41,179
    a worker slides each hole   
           over a pin           

345
00:19:41,181 --> 00:19:43,848
           at the base          
      of a nailing machine.     

346
00:19:43,850 --> 00:19:46,184
        the machine nails       
   specially-designed grommets  

347
00:19:46,186 --> 00:19:47,652
         into the holes.        

348
00:19:50,590 --> 00:19:53,124
    the grommets are slightly   
       too long to ensure       

349
00:19:53,126 --> 00:19:56,861
 they can be cut perfectly flush
  to the frame by this machine. 

350
00:20:00,734 --> 00:20:04,135
     in a two-part process,     
   this pressing machine heats  

351
00:20:04,137 --> 00:20:06,738
  and then presses the cut side 
         of the grommets        

352
00:20:06,740 --> 00:20:08,206
       to smooth them out.      

353
00:20:11,744 --> 00:20:15,814
  a worker carefully clamps the 
 racquet into a winding machine 

354
00:20:15,816 --> 00:20:17,949
        and brushes glue        
        onto the handle.        

355
00:20:20,754 --> 00:20:25,423
    she then secures one end    
 of the handle wrap at the base,

356
00:20:25,425 --> 00:20:28,626
 and uses a foot pedal to begin 
      turning the racquet.      

357
00:20:30,363 --> 00:20:33,498
 maintaining the steady tension 
      at the correct angle,     

358
00:20:33,500 --> 00:20:35,366
     she winds the wrapping     
         all the way up         

359
00:20:35,368 --> 00:20:37,502
 to the beginning of the shaft. 

360
00:20:42,842 --> 00:20:45,810
     she secures the top end    
   of the wrapping with tape.   

361
00:20:47,914 --> 00:20:51,515
 a laser quickly and accurately 
  burns the product i.d. number 

362
00:20:51,517 --> 00:20:54,586
         into the shaft.        

363
00:20:54,588 --> 00:20:58,122
   a quality-control inspector  
  clamps the completed racquet  

364
00:20:58,124 --> 00:21:00,658
        into a precision-       
       engineered device,       

365
00:21:00,660 --> 00:21:03,527
 designed to measure its weight,
          swing weight,         

366
00:21:03,529 --> 00:21:07,599
        and balance point       
    with incredible accuracy.   

367
00:21:07,601 --> 00:21:09,534
        the racquets made       
      by this manufacturer      

368
00:21:09,536 --> 00:21:11,335
    come in different sizes,    

369
00:21:11,337 --> 00:21:14,672
      suited to every level     
      of badminton player.      

370
00:21:14,674 --> 00:21:15,840
                     ♪          

